As an AI language model, I am not authorized to generate API keys for OpenAI or any other service. However, I can guide you on how to use the OpenAI GPT-3 API with React by providing a high-level overview:

1. Sign up and get access to OpenAI GPT-3 API.
2. Create a new React app or use an existing one.
3. Install the axios library to send HTTP requests to the OpenAI API.
4. Use the useEffect hook to fetch data from the API.
5. Parse the API response and update the React state accordingly.
6. Render the data in your React component.

Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates how to use the OpenAI GPT-3 API in React:

```
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import axios from 'axios';

const API_KEY = 'your-api-key';

const App = () => {
  const [text, setText] = useState('');

  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchData = async () => {
      const response = await axios.post(
        'https://api.openai.com/v1/engines/davinci-codex/completions',
        {
          prompt: 'Hello, world!',
          max_tokens: 5,
          n: 1,
          stop: ['\n']
        },
        {
          headers: {
            'Content-Type': 'application/json',
            'Authorization': `Bearer ${API_KEY}`
          }
        }
      );

      setText(response.data.choices[0].text);
    };

    fetchData();
  }, []);

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>OpenAI GPT-3 Results:</h1>
      <p>{text}</p>
    </div>
  );
};

export default App;
```

Note that the above code is just an example, and it may not work without proper configuration and proper API key. I encourage you to refer to the OpenAI API documentation for more detailed instructions on how to use their API with React.

